This file tracks the status of releases in the 1.3.x line.

See "Stabilizing and maintaining releases" in trunk/www/hacking.html for
details on how release lines and voting work, what kinds of bugs can
delay a release, etc.

Status of 1.3.0:
================

Candidate changes:

  * r16350
    Fix issue #1911, where svndumpfilter generated invalid dumpfiles
    when copies occurred and --drop-empty-revs and --renumber-revs
    were in use.
    Justification:
      Invalid dumpfiles are not nice.
    Votes:
      +1: cmpilato, kfogel
      +0: dlr (concept, new to this area of the code)

  * r16722, r16727, r16728
    Duplicate objects passed to callbacks in the Ruby bindings to avoid
    pool-related scoping issues.
    Justification:
      Fixes segfaults in the Ruby test suite.
    Votes:
      +1: kou
      +1: djames(r16722)

  * r16725
    Enable running autogen.sh with Python <2.1, in which the scope of
    variables within lambda is restricted.
    Justification:
      Build failure due only to the scope issue of old Python is not good.
    Votes:
      +0: nori

Approved changes:
